Lagos – A 27-year-old man,  Kabiru Yusuf, on Monday, appeared before an Ebute Meta Magistrates’ Court, Lagos for allegedly stabbing one Moses Tobi with a broken bottle and a knife. Yusuf is facing a two-count charge of conspiracy and assault to which he pleaded not guilty. The prosecutor, ASP Clara Olagbayi, told the court that the accused 
committed the offences on Jan. 30, at 9.30 p.m. at Agege Railway
Station. Olagbayi said that the defendant used broken bottle and the knife to commit the act. The offences contravened Sections 173 and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The Magistrate, Mrs O.A. Olagbende, admitted the accused to bail in
the sum of N10,000 with one surety in like sum and adjourned the case
until Feb. 12.